.TH GETUSERSHELL 3  "November 8, 1985"
.UC 6
.SH NAME
getusershell, setusershell, endusershell \- get legal user shells
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B char *getusershell()
.PP
.B setusershell()
.PP
.B endusershell()
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Getusershell
returns a pointer to a legal user shell as defined by the
system manager in the file 
.IR /etc/shells .
If 
.I /etc/shells
does not exist, the two standard system shells
.I /bin/sh
and
.I /bin/csh
are returned.
.PP
.I Getusershell
reads the next
line (opening the file if necessary);
.I setusershell
rewinds the file;
.I endusershell
closes it.
.SH FILES
/etc/shells
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
The routine
.I getusershell
returns a null pointer (0) on EOF or error.
.SH BUGS
All information
is contained in a static area
so it must be copied if it is
to be saved.
